tiv>Stiv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#660000>(7/6/01 2:38:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Problems with MA's</span><hr size=1> Currently I play a level 25 Atrox MA. Most of my hits are in the high 20s and low 30s unbuffed. I do brawls for anywhere from 50 to 160(rare). I was fairly happy with my character until an enforcer I group with got 2 very nice swords. He now hits for anywhere from 60 to 130 regularly. He is within 2 levels of me and he does twice the damage. How can MA's compete with this? Enforcers have more HP's and with the right equipment do much more damage. With very average swords enforcers do as much or a little less damage then MA's at this level. This leads me to believe one of two things. We are basically a broken class and just plain suck as long as enforcers and other professions keep up on they're gear OR we become usefull and powerful later on. I believe its the first one because enforcers and the like will continue to get good weapons as they move on and we will be stuck with fists. The only possibilities of becoming half usefull seem to be either starting to use weapons or just changing professions. I realize its early in the game and I am early in the game so I am not going to quit MA. I was just hoping someone on this board would say &quot;I played a ma in beta 3 to level 183 and your wrong&quot; so all of you experienced players please reply here. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=byteme>byteme</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#660000>(7/6/01 2:43:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Problems with MA's</span><hr size=1> No answer for you from me, just wanted to respond with &quot;that sounds really sucky.&quot; Hope we turn out better then. Although, I am better then my Agent friends  =)     but, &quot;second place is just first loser&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uvnine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VNine</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif  BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#660000>(7/6/01 3:05:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Problems with MA's</span><hr size=1> I've read that MAs are the second best healers aside from doctors. So, I'm assuming that are solo ability may be better than that of an enforcer.  I think it would be cool if MAs could use swords like katanas...but that's another topic. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/umobleyq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mobleyq</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#660000>(7/6/01 3:10:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Problems with MA's</span><hr size=1> His attacks did twice as much.  But how often did he hit?<br>
<br>
I'm not here to troll, but are you that concerned about how much damage you do compared to another class already?<br>
<br>
I played an enforcer in beta, and I can tell you, they don't get Dimach (unless they forgo ALOT of IP).<br>
<br>
Just wanting to take a look at how &quot;sucky&quot; this really is from an overal outlook.  Didn't seem like all things where taken into consideration.<br>
<br>
I was wondering one more thing.  How do you do soloing etc.?  I mean, if you suck you suck.  Regardless of how badarse someone else near your level becomes through other means.  Do you feel like you contribute to your groups?<br>
<br>
I guess my point is, instead of letting what the guy next to you is doing determine how sucky or badarse you feel, just play and let your own experiences dictate.<br>
<br>
