<br>
I dont think we are that far away from them ,,but there's one other thing we are very good at which IMO makes us very worthwhile ,is our Healing abilities ,,apparently second only to a Doctor.<br>
<br>
Come on a tank that can dish out the damage and then heal as well .Thats gotta be good aint it? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=genjuro>Genjuro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#660000>(7/6/01 6:21:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Problems with MA's</span><hr size=1> Ahhhhh.... <br>
<br>
   Grasshopers. What some of us fail to recall is that the martial arts description say... &quot;It can do alot of damage at the high levels.&quot;  I will repeat. High levels. Don't take this the wrong way, but 25th level out of 200 is still pretty small. <br>
When I decided to become a martial arts. I had a guess that at some point weapons would catch up, or out damage my combat ability. Why did I choose the MA? Simple. Bright greens in every single dodge skill. <br>
<br>
    We are hard to hit. Also consider we are working at 100%<br>
effiency every level with bare hands. The plus of that is we don't need ammo (unless your REALLY like the bow). The minus is we can't upgrade. So in damage output terms. We will probably be short next to weapons. That's ok. We have other advantages to take use of. A) Our defense. It is the best hands down, all other combat classes have light blue, we have light green. B) Dual weild has chance to hit penalties. Thus we forsake tons of damage per hit, for much more accurate hits. C) Our nano skills. We aren't far behind in our choices of casting ablities. We aren't far behind in our ability to heal. D) Run speed. We are one of THE fastest professions, and we are faster than the other 2 combat classes. <br>
<br>
     Those are just a few I can think of. If you thought that the MA would out damage all your friends from level 1 to level 200. You picked the wrong class. The soldiers are a combat class entirely focused on range combat. The enforcer is focused on upclose fun. We the Martial artist, are a sort of jack of all trades in the combat area. We have ranged capablity that the enforcer doesn't, but isn't as fast as the soldier. We have melee ability the soldier doesn't but in cases might not be as good as a well equiped enforcer. <br>
<br>
    This is my perception of the profession. So far I like. I can solo things due to my buffs, and heals. I can also fill a nice niche in groups. Good profession if you under stand it's place in the cycle of life.<br>
<br>
Genjuro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=stiv>Stiv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#660000>(7/6/01 9:12:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Problems with MA's</span><hr size=1> Like I said, I am not ruling MA's out at all. I realize that I have yet to even scratch the surface of AO's and levels and whatnot.<br>
<br>
