<br>
I did overlook our healing skills. Thats true we can heal during combat and that helps us out a lot. I am going to stick with it of course and hope that later on we will be the best melee damage dealers hands down. If thats not the case I am still not going to quit because I have fun with the game and thats what it all comes down to. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/usyldin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syldin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#660000>(7/6/01 9:28:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Problems with MA's</span><hr size=1> What swords are these ?<br>
<br>
Quality 33 edgeless e-blade does 4-56 not 60-130, and you would need to be level 29 to equip it without buffs or implants.<br>
<br>
